    <body>
        <p>After you add items to a cell, you can nest them by using the left and right arrows. If an item is above and to the left of other items, it becomes the parent; the child items are below and to the right of the parent. When this occurs, the child items inherit the settings from the parent item (e.g., link type).</p>
        <ol class="LowerAlpha">
            <li>Click on a topic link in a cell that you want to move.</li>
            <li>In the local toolbar, click <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Ca-Co-Fl-Li-Mi/Interface/Buttons/Move-Item-Left-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> to move it to the left, or click <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Ca-Co-Fl-Li-Mi/Interface/Buttons/Move-Item-Right-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> to move it to the right. </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>